{"title":"HPmon","url":"https://nethackwiki.com/wiki/HPmon","type":"markdown","data":"| **HPmon**                                                                |                                                      |\n| ------------------------------------------------------------------------ | ---------------------------------------------------- |\n| Author                                                                   | Ralph Churchill                                      |\n| Download                                                                 | [link](http://www.netsonic.fi/~walker/nh/hpmon.diff) |\n| [NetHack PatchDB](/wiki/NetHack_Patch_Database \"NetHack Patch Database\") | [45](http://nhpatchdb.alt.org/?45)                   |\n\nThe **Hpmon** or **HPmon** patch adds a color display to your [HP](/wiki/HP \"HP\") meter. This patch is only for [tty](/wiki/Tty \"Tty\") users.\n\nAs you fight monsters, if your HP meter turns yellow, then turns red, then becomes highlighted or blinking, then you know that you are approaching [death](/wiki/Death_\\(character\\) \"Death (character)\") and requiring [healing](/wiki/Healing \"Healing\") or [rest](/wiki/Rest \"Rest\"). This patch makes no change to gameplay but can save your life!\n\nHPmon is also popular because [nethack.alt.org](/wiki/Nethack.alt.org \"Nethack.alt.org\") had it (NAO switched on 2012-05-19 to [statuscolors](/wiki/Statuscolors \"Statuscolors\")). (The version there sometimes fails to color the HP meter; this might be a bug after resolving the conflict with the [dumplog](/wiki/Dumplog \"Dumplog\") patch.) [GruntHack](/wiki/GruntHack \"GruntHack\") has an expanded version of it.\n\nCompare with the [statuscolors](/wiki/Statuscolors \"Statuscolors\") patch, which extends HPmon to color several parts of the status line but requires user configuration.\n\n[Status\\_hilites](/wiki/Status_hilites \"Status hilites\") can also color the HitPoints in 3.6.\n","html":"<!DOCTYPE html>\n<html class=\"client-